<subSubSection id="C36BB195FF81FFDFB7E173822BE7F8EA" pageId="2" pageNumber="153" type="description">
<paragraph id="8BCEE21EFF81FFDFB7E173822CC9F81C" blockId="2.[113,765,1726,1942]" pageId="2" pageNumber="153">
<emphasis id="B9053E0CFF81FFDFB7E173822F34F95C" box="[151,257,1726,1750]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="153">History. –</emphasis>
In the protologue 
<bibRefCitation id="EFE09FEFFF81FFDFB6BE73822C53F95C" author="VISIANI, R. DE" box="[456,614,1726,1750]" pageId="2" pageNumber="153" pagination="113 - 115" refId="ref2560" refString="VISIANI, R. DE (1865). Di un nuovo giglio nella Dalmazia. Amico Campi 1: 113 - 115." type="journal article" year="1865">VISIANI (1865)</bibRefCitation>
distinguished this 
<taxonomicName id="4C71999DFF81FFDFB7E973E22F17F97C" box="[159,290,1758,1782]" pageId="2" pageNumber="153" rank="variety" variety="from">variety from</taxonomicName>
typical 
<taxonomicName id="4C71999DFF81FFDFB60F73E22FC3F97C" box="[377,502,1758,1782]" class="Liliopsida" family="Liliaceae" genus="Lilium" kingdom="Plantae" order="Liliales" pageId="2" pageNumber="153" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="martagon">
<emphasis id="B9053E0CFF81FFDFB60F73E22FC3F97C" box="[377,502,1758,1782]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="153">L.martagon</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
L. in having “ 
<emphasis id="B9053E0CFF81FFDFB5EE73E22CC0F89C" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="153">L. phyllis perianthii extus glaberrimis, intus rubro-venosis unicoloribus”</emphasis>
. In PAD we traced a specimen (individual on the left side) having the original Visiani’s autograph description of this taxon which is identical to the description given in the protologue. Moreover, Visiani refers to 
<taxonomicName id="4C71999DFF81FFDFB6ED72422C65F81C" authority="de Cattani" authorityName="de Cattani" box="[411,592,1918,1942]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Moraceae" genus="Maria" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" order="Rosales" pageId="2" pageNumber="153" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">Maria de Cattani</taxonomicName>
as the collector
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BCEE21EFF81FFDFB43171DD2A1CFA85" blockId="2.[839,1491,1216,1295]" pageId="2" pageNumber="153">
[
<taxonomicName id="4C71999DFF81FFDFB43B71DD2DE7FB7F" authority="de Cattani" authorityName="de Cattani" box="[845,978,1249,1269]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Moraceae" genus="Maria" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" order="Rosales" pageId="2" pageNumber="153" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">Maria de Cattani</taxonomicName>
s.n., PAD] [© Erbario Patavinum, Università degli Studi di Padova. Reproduced with permission]
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BCEE21EFF81FFDFB431705C2A41F9D2" blockId="2.[838,1490,1376,1624]" pageId="2" pageNumber="153">
<materialsCitation id="3B19E843FF81FFDFB431705C2A45F9D2" country="Croatia" location="On" municipality="Biokovo" pageId="2" pageNumber="153" specimenCount="1" typeStatus="lectotype">
and Much (Muć) locality (
<collectingCountry id="F366A28EFF81FFDFB329705C2A85FAF2" box="[1119,1200,1376,1400]" name="Croatia" pageId="2" pageNumber="153">Croatia</collectingCountry>
) as the collection site, both of which are mentioned on the herbarium label. Thus this specimen can be considered as original material collected from the “locus classicus” and is designated here as the 
<typeStatus id="54CA5CBCFF81FFDFB21170FC2BF8FA52" box="[1383,1485,1472,1496]" pageId="2" pageNumber="153">lectotype</typeStatus>
. 
<location id="8EAEB4C5FF81FFDFB43170DC2D5DFA72" LSID="urn:lsid:plazi:treatment:03D85308FF82FFDFB71476832BE7F8EA:8EAEB4C5FF81FFDFB43170DC2D5DFA72" box="[839,872,1504,1528]" country="Croatia" municipality="Biokovo" name="On" pageId="2" pageNumber="153">On</location>
the same herbarium sheet (specimen on the right side) is also a plant referable to 
<taxonomicName id="4C71999DFF81FFDFB325733C2AE9F992" box="[1107,1244,1536,1560]" class="Liliopsida" family="Liliaceae" genus="Lilium" kingdom="Plantae" order="Liliales" pageId="2" pageNumber="153" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="martagon">
<emphasis id="B9053E0CFF81FFDFB325733C2AE9F992" box="[1107,1244,1536,1560]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="153">L. martagon</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
collected on 
<collectingMunicipality id="6BAA7864FF81FFDFB204733C2BE4F992" box="[1394,1489,1536,1560]" pageId="2" pageNumber="153">Biokovo</collectingMunicipality>
(
<collectingCountry id="F366A28EFF81FFDFB439731C2D9CF9B2" box="[847,937,1568,1592]" name="Croatia" pageId="2" pageNumber="153">Croatia</collectingCountry>
): “ 
<taxonomicName id="4C71999DFF81FFDFB4B1731C2A97F9B2" authority="Martagon L." authorityName="Martagon L." box="[967,1186,1568,1592]" class="Liliopsida" family="Liliaceae" genus="Lilium" kingdom="Plantae" order="Liliales" pageId="2" pageNumber="153" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B9053E0CFF81FFDFB4B1731C2AB6F9B2" box="[967,1155,1568,1592]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="153">Lilium Martagon</emphasis>
L.
</taxonomicName>
/ In umbrosis sylvatices mt Biokovo / Visiani s.d., s.n.”
</materialsCitation>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BCEE21EFF81FFDFB41B73542BE7F8EA" blockId="2.[839,1490,1640,1888]" pageId="2" pageNumber="153">
<emphasis id="B9053E0CFF81FFDFB41B73542A5AF90A" box="[877,1135,1640,1664]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="153">Taxonomic discussion. –</emphasis>
The selected 
<typeStatus id="54CA5CBCFF81FFDFB27773542B57F90A" box="[1281,1378,1640,1664]" pageId="2" pageNumber="153">lectotype</typeStatus>
fully confirms the close relationship between 
<taxonomicName id="4C71999DFF81FFDFB3C973B42B0BF92A" box="[1215,1342,1672,1696]" class="Liliopsida" family="Liliaceae" genus="Lilium" kingdom="Plantae" order="Liliales" pageId="2" pageNumber="153" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="martagon">
<emphasis id="B9053E0CFF81FFDFB3C973B42B0BF92A" box="[1215,1342,1672,1696]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="153">L. martagon</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="4C71999DFF81FFDFB20673B42A3CF94A" class="Liliopsida" family="Liliaceae" genus="Lilium" kingdom="Plantae" order="Liliales" pageId="2" pageNumber="153" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="variety" species="martagon" variety="cattaniae">
<emphasis id="B9053E0CFF81FFDFB20673B42D45F94A" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="153">L. martagon</emphasis>
var. 
<emphasis id="B9053E0CFF81FFDFB4D273942A3CF94A" box="[932,1033,1704,1728]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="153">cattaniae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and therefore the varietal rank is the most appropriate, which is also suggested by recent molecular analysis as it failed to distinguish the two taxa at a specific level (
<bibRefCitation id="EFE09FEFFF81FFDFB43872342A76F8AA" author="MURATOVIC, E. &amp; HIDALGO, T." box="[846,1091,1800,1824]" pageId="2" pageNumber="153" pagination="180 - 189" refId="ref2294" refString="MURATOVIC, E., O. HIDALGO, T. GARNATJE &amp; S. SILJAK- YAKOVLEV (2010). Molecular phylogeny and genome size in European lilies (genus Lilium, Liliaceae). Advanced Sci. Lett. 3: 180 - 189." type="journal article" year="2010">MURATOVIĆ &amp; al., 2010</bibRefCitation>
). The Linnaean taxon 
<taxonomicName id="4C71999DFF81FFDFB25372342B96F8AA" box="[1317,1443,1800,1824]" class="Liliopsida" family="Liliaceae" genus="Lilium" kingdom="Plantae" order="Liliales" pageId="2" pageNumber="153" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="martagon">
<emphasis id="B9053E0CFF81FFDFB25372342B96F8AA" box="[1317,1443,1800,1824]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="153">L. martagon</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
was also recently typified by PERUZZI &amp; JARVIS (2009) and the specimen from LINN (sheet No. 420.5) was selected as 
<typeStatus id="54CA5CBCFF81FFDFB21C72742BFAF8EA" box="[1386,1487,1864,1888]" pageId="2" pageNumber="153">lectotype</typeStatus>
.
</paragraph>
